# Environment Setup Guide

This guide walks you through setting up your local development environment for the **Barista Coffee Membership** project.  
For: BA, Developer, Tester joining the project.

---

## Prerequisites

- macOS computer
- Internet connection
- GitHub account — create for free at [github.com](https://github.com)
- Anthropic/Claude account — create for free at [claude.ai](https://claude.ai)

---

## Step 1 — Check Node.js

Node.js is required to run BMad (the project workflow framework).

Open **Terminal** (Cmd + Space → type "Terminal" → Enter), then run:

```bash
node --version
```

**Expected output:** A version number such as `v22.x.x`

- ✅ Version number appears → already installed, move to Step 2
- ❌ `command not found` → install Node.js:
  1. Go to [nodejs.org](https://nodejs.org)
  2. Download the **LTS** version
  3. Install normally (Next → Next → Install)
  4. Run `node --version` again to confirm

---

## Step 2 — Set Up Your IDE

You need an AI-powered IDE to work on this project. There are two options:

**Option A — Kiro IDE (recommended, used by this project)**
1. Go to [kiro.dev](https://kiro.dev) → download and install
2. Open Kiro
3. Sign in with your Anthropic/Claude account

**Option B — Terminal only**
- Install Claude Code by running:
  ```bash
  npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code
  ```
- Sign in with your Anthropic/Claude account when prompted
- All work is done via terminal commands

**Expected output:** Kiro opens successfully and you are logged in, or `claude --version` returns a version number in terminal.

---

## Step 3 — Accept GitHub Invitation

> Applies to invited collaborators only (not the repo owner)

1. Check your email for a message from GitHub titled *"You've been invited to collaborate"*
2. Click **Accept invitation**
3. You will be redirected to the `barista-coffee-membership` repo on GitHub

**Expected output:** You can see the `barista-coffee-membership` repository on GitHub without any access error.

---

## Step 4 — Clone the Repository

Open Terminal and run the following commands one by one:

```bash
cd ~/Desktop
git clone https://github.com/htrang-189/barista-coffee-membership.git
cd barista-coffee-membership
```

**Expected output:**
```
Receiving objects: 100% (xxx/xxx), done.
htrang@MacBook barista-coffee-membership %
```

---

## Step 5 — Open the Project in Kiro

> Skip this step if you are using Terminal only (Option B above)

1. Open Kiro
2. Go to **File → Open Folder**
3. Select the `barista-coffee-membership` folder on your Desktop
4. The project files will appear in the left panel

**Expected output:** Left panel shows folders `.claude` and `_bmad` — setup is complete. ✅

---

## Project Structure

```
barista-coffee-membership/
├── README.md                         ← Project overview
├── docs/
│   └── SETUP.md                      ← This file
├── .claude/
│   └── skills/                       ← 44 BMad skills (agents, workflows)
└── _bmad/
    └── _bmad-output/
        ├── planning-artifacts/       ← PRD, Architecture documents
        └── implementation-artifacts/ ← Sprint, Stories
```

